interjection: 1. Used alone to tell other people to stop doing what they are doing, especially talking or generally making a commotion.
verbLexeme: 1. To stop a fire burning or a light shining. English = extinguish, turn off (light), put out (fire).
2. To be no longer burning (fire) or shining (light). English = (be) off (light), (be) out (fire).
3. To shut or close a beak-like or mouth-like object.
nominalLexeme: 1. The ending of the burning of a fire or the shining of a light; the turning off of a light; the putting out of a fire.
3. A beak-like or mouth-like object, or its action of closing.
